description.plain:
Julia Michaels, originally Julia Carin Cavazos, was born in Davenport, Iowa in 1993, and moved to Santa Clarita, California, north of Los Angeles, with her family. She began singing at age 12.

She’s written many successful pop songs. In her late teens she met songwriters Joleen Belle and Lindy Robbins, with whom she wrote “Fire Starter” for Demi Lovato and “Miss Movin' On” for Fifth Harmony. Other credits include Selena Gomez’s “Slow Down” and “Good for You”, and Justin Bieber’s “Sorry”.

Michaels formalized a deal with music publishing powerhouse Warner-Chappell. Her debut single, “Issues”, was released on January 13, 2017, and reached 11 on Billboard’s US Hot 100.

songs.title: Issues

description.plain:
“Issues” is an upbeat anthem about a relationship between people who have “issues,” but love each other enough to work past them.

Although the track is Julia Michaels' debut single, it’s not her first visit to the pop charts. She wrote “Good For You” for Selena Gomez, “Sorry” for Justin Bieber, and “All In My Head (Flex)” for Fifth Harmony. She also collaborated on Zedd’s True Colors album and lent her vocals to Kygo’s “Carry Me,” which she sung at the 2016 Rio Olympic Games.

The track gained lots of buzz after her friend and studio buddy Selena Gomez posted an Instagram video of them dancing to the track.

On March 20, 2017, this single had its TV debut in a live performance on The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, thereby also marking the first TV performance for Julia Michaels.

The music video was released on March 7, 2017.

On November 28th, 2017, the song was officially nominated under the Song of the Year category, making it Michaels' first solo single as a lead artist to receive a Grammy nomination.

songs.title: Heaven

description.plain:
“Heaven” is a part of the Fifty Shades Freed original soundtrack. The song was written by Julia Michaels, MNEK and Tayla Parx, who are also credited as the producers.

The song describes “bad boys” as having a duplicitous and sinful nature, bringing heaven to their lover and keeping them forever attached. The lyrics, overall, have many religious and spiritual innuendos.

songs.full_title: Anxiety by Julia Michaels (Ft. Selena Gomez)
songs.title: Anxiety

description.plain:
“Anxiety” is the intro to Michaels' second studio EP, Inner Monologue.

Michaels has always been vocal about her mental health problems, and even wrote a touching piece about anxiety for the magazine Glamour.

Michaels shared a demo of the song with Rolling Stone, who described it as a “campfire strum supported by a heartbeat bassline”.

In the song, produced by longtime collaborator and Grammy winner producer Ian Kirkpatrick, Michaels sings her personal experience on living with anxiety, her sleepless nights, hearing from exes and refusing her doctor’s advice to take medicine.
